Found an issue with Example 3 with Python3. I wrote a solution that uses DFS but I get the utput `[[4],[9,5],[3,0,1],[2,8],[7]]` instead of `[[4],[9,5],[3,0,1],[8,2],[7]]`. I created this tree locally in my workstation and ran my code which outputed the correct solution `[[4],[9,5],[3,0,1],[8,2],[7]]`.
I also debugged the code in the leetcode debugger and it looks like the node with the values `2` is connected to the node with the value `0` instead of the node with the value `1`.

A simple DFS code to see the issue.
```
class Solution:
    def verticalOrder(self, root: Optional[TreeNode]) -> List[List[int]]:
        def dfs(node: Optional[TreeNode]):
            if not node:
                return

            dfs(node.left)
            dfs(node.right)

        dfs(root)
```
